@startuml remote_climate_to_datc_hvac_output_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Remote Climate To DATC HVAC Output Signal Flow\n(TMU/cabin-air context -> DATC HVAC state and actuator publish)

participant "TMU / cabin-air inputs" as ClimateCtx #F4F7FB
participant "DATC\nHVAC owner" as DATC #E8F7E8
participant "HVAC state / actuator bus" as HvacBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / comfort users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== HVAC Inputs ==

ClimateCtx -> DATC : remoteClimateReq\ntmuLinkState\ntmuServiceMode\nsignalBars\ncabinTemp
DATC -> DATC : if TMU stale then\nremoteClimateReq = 0 / link = 0 / service = 0
DATC -> DATC : if cabin-air stale then\ncabinTemp = 24
DATC -> DATC : derive CabinSetTemp / BlowerLevel / AcOn / VentMode / DefogMode
note right of DATC
Representative gating inputs
- remoteClimateReq
- tmuLinkState / serviceMode
- signalBars
- cabinTemp
end note

== HVAC Publish ==

DATC -> HvacBus : frmHvacStateMsg\nCabinSetTemp / BlowerLevel / AcCompressorOn
DATC -> HvacBus : frmHvacActuatorMsg\nVentMode / RecircMode / DefogMode / FanRpmStep
note right of DATC
Representative outputs
- CabinSetTemp
- BlowerLevel
- AcCompressorOn
- VentMode / DefogMode
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

HvacBus -> Obs : HVAC readback /\ncomfort-service consumers

note over ClimateCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. TMU remote-climate and cabin-air context reach DATC
2. DATC decides HVAC state and actuator targets
3. DATC publishes HVAC state and actuator frames
4. Comfort users and observers consume the effective HVAC posture
end note

@enduml
